{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a75f31bf3a7b0d04a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are scanning ~/dharma_swarm/ for philosophical, architectural, and design content relevant to the \"Telos Engine\" — NOT code, but the IDEAS embedded in the codebase.\n\nRead and analyze:\n1. ~/dharma_swarm/CLAUDE.md — the thinkodynamic CLAUDE.md with triple mapping, colony intelligence, shakti framework, v7 rules, system self-map\n2. Any README.md or design docs in the repo\n3. Docstrings and module-level comments in key files that explain WHY decisions were made:\n   - dharma_swarm/ontology.py (1,348 lines) — typed ontology, 8 ObjectTypes\n   - dharma_swarm/decision_ontology.py (470 lines) — decision artifacts\n   - dharma_swarm/logic_layer.py (819 lines) — Palantir AIP-style logic\n   - dharma_swarm/guardrails.py (575 lines) — Anduril-style autonomy levels\n   - dharma_swarm/lineage.py (462 lines) — Palantir Funnel-inspired provenance\n4. The telos gate system: hooks/telos_gate.py\n5. Any files referencing Palantir, Anduril, or enterprise system lessons\n\nFor each significant finding, report:\n- Source location\n- Key ideas/principles extracted\n- Where it maps to in telos-engine/ (foundations/, architecture/, seeds/)\n- What's UNIQUE here that doesn't exist elsewhere\n\nFocus on extracting the PRINCIPLES and DESIGN RATIONALE, not implementation details.\n\nDO NOT write any code or create any files. This is RESEARCH ONLY."},"uuid":"807929d7-4965-4d82-ae73-f1eda2d09dca","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:13.518Z","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
