{"parentUuid":"1e8c6e48-f796-4d41-ab4d-6ee5df97f3fc","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"74ab6cc1-259e-4f35-896b-31737bc09d28","agentId":"a75f31bf3a7b0d04a","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015WXELw7cv3Y9Q6ZS958bZx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→document_id: dse-architecture-map\n     3→title: Dharmic Singularity Engine Architecture Map\n     4→status: ACTIVE\n     5→system: DHARMA SWARM\n     6→component: Dharmic Singularity Engine\n     7→doc_type: architecture_map\n     8→created: \"2026-03-10\"\n     9→last_modified: \"2026-03-10\"\n    10→owners:\n    11→  - Codex\n    12→tags:\n    13→  - dse\n    14→  - architecture\n    15→  - integration\n    16→external_sources:\n    17→  - path: /Users/dhyana/Downloads/dharmic_singularity_engine_mega_prompt.md\n    18→    role: target_architecture\n    19→connections:\n    20→  upstream:\n    21→    - docs/dse/DSE_FOUNDATIONS_SUMMARY.md\n    22→  peers:\n    23→    - docs/dse/DSE_PHASE_ROADMAP.md\n    24→    - docs/dse/DSE_TEST_INVARIANTS.md\n    25→  downstream:\n    26→    - docs/dse/packets/PHASE_01_SELF_OBSERVATION_MONAD.md\n    27→    - docs/dse/packets/PHASE_02_COALGEBRAIC_EVOLUTION.md\n    28→    - docs/dse/packets/PHASE_03_INFORMATION_GEOMETRY.md\n    29→    - docs/dse/packets/PHASE_04_SHEAF_COORDINATION.md\n    30→---\n    31→\n    32→# Architecture Map\n    33→\n    34→This file maps the Dharmic Singularity Engine concept onto the current `dharma_swarm` codebase. The mega prompt's file sizes are stale; the table below reflects the repo as of March 10, 2026.\n    35→\n    36→## Existing Modules\n    37→\n    38→| Module | Current Size | Current Role | Target DSE Role | Early Strategy |\n    39→|---|---:|---|---|---|\n    40→| `dharma_swarm/rv.py` | 426 | R_V measurement, reading model, correlator support | measurement engine inside the self-observation monad | wrap, do not replace |\n    41→| `dharma_swarm/evolution.py` | 1896 | Darwin orchestration, proposal lifecycle, drift review | internal substrate for coalgebraic stepping | adapt via wrapper |\n    42→| `dharma_swarm/archive.py` | 509 | lineage, fitness, archive persistence | carrier of trajectory observations and promotion state | extend compatibly |\n    43→| `dharma_swarm/elegance.py` | 345 | code elegance scoring | fitness projection inside coalgebra observations | reuse |\n    44→| `dharma_swarm/metrics.py` | 410 | behavioral signatures | observation manifold features and bridge inputs | reuse |\n    45→| `dharma_swarm/bridge.py` | 583 | RV to behavior correlation | naturality/consistency seam between mechanistic and behavioral signals | extend lightly |\n    46→| `dharma_swarm/monitor.py` | 510 | anomaly detection | source for drift and instability signals | reuse |\n    47→| `dharma_swarm/telos_gates.py` | 586 | dharmic gate checks | invariant-preserving transition filter | preserve |\n    48→| `dharma_swarm/selector.py` | 241 | parent selection | selection morphism inside evolution wrapper | reuse |\n    49→| `dharma_swarm/fitness_predictor.py` | 243 | predictive scoring | meta-evolution input surface | reuse |\n    50→| `dharma_swarm/providers.py` | 1519 | provider routing and policy surface | later target for paradigm/topos phases, not Phase 1 | leave alone for now |\n    51→\n    52→## New Modules Proposed by the Mega Prompt\n    53→\n    54→| Proposed Module | Purpose | Recommended Delivery Mode |\n    55→|---|---|---|\n    56→| `dharma_swarm/monad.py` | self-observation monad over current RV machinery | implement first |\n    57→| `dharma_swarm/coalgebra.py` | observation wrapper over Darwin evolution | implement second |\n    58→| `dharma_swarm/info_geometry.py` | geometric meta-evolution | implemented as a stdlib-first adapter over `MetaParameters` and `meta_evolution.py` |\n    59→| `dharma_swarm/sheaf.py` | multi-agent consistency and obstruction tracking | implemented over `AgentState`, `Message`, and `anekanta_gate` |\n    60→| `dharma_swarm/godel_engine.py` | controlled paradigm shifts | defer until policy/context boundaries are explicit |\n    61→| `dharma_swarm/adjunction.py` | typed inter-layer composition | defer until earlier structures exist |\n    62→\n    63→## Critical Repo Reality Gaps\n    64→\n    65→### 1. No Canonical `SystemState`\n    66→\n    67→The mega prompt assumes a single `SystemState`. The repo does not currently define one. Early DSE work should therefore use typed wrappers over existing values:\n    68→\n    69→- `RVReading`\n    70→- `Proposal`\n    71→- `ArchiveEntry`\n    72→- serializable mappings or typed snapshots\n    73→\n    74→Do not invent a giant universal state object in Phase 1.\n    75→\n    76→### 2. `evolution.py` Is Already Rich and Large\n    77→\n    78→The mega prompt describes a 447-line `evolution.py`. The real file is 1896 lines and already contains retrospective and drift logic. The correct move is an adapter layer, not a ground-up refactor.\n    79→\n    80→### 3. Behavior Already Matters\n    81→\n    82→The repo already contains a mechanistic-to-behavior bridge. That makes the DSE framing stronger, because it can build on an existing observational seam instead of introducing one from scratch.\n    83→\n    84→## Recommended Layering\n    85→\n    86→```text\n    87→rv.py\n    88→  -> monad.py\n    89→     -> coalgebra.py\n    90→        -> info_geometry.py\n    91→        -> sheaf.py\n    92→        -> godel_engine.py\n    93→           -> adjunction.py\n    94→```\n    95→\n    96→This keeps the later layers dependent on explicit interfaces rather than directly on the internal structure of `evolution.py`.\n    97→\n    98→## File Boundary Guidance\n    99→\n   100→For the next implementation passes:\n   101→\n   102→- Phase 1 should stay close to `rv.py`, `bridge.py`, and new tests.\n   103→- Phase 2 should wrap `evolution.py` and touch archive types only where needed for observation surfaces.\n   104→- `providers.py` should remain out of scope until a later phase explicitly targets paradigm or routing abstractions.\n   105→"}]},"uuid":"c4e0bdca-3bf9-4305-bc6c-a67f8628d6f6","timestamp":"2026-03-15T13:46:32.432Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"1e8c6e48-f796-4d41-ab4d-6ee5df97f3fc","userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/dhyana","sessionId":"2ea96bb4-afee-473b-8609-a3975acc2c75","version":"2.1.76","gitBranch":"HEAD","slug":"shimmering-leaping-badger"}
